LOCK TABLES `artifacts` WRITE;
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `artifacts` DISABLE KEYS */;
INSERT INTO `artifacts` VALUES (8,'Fish and net patterns frequently appear on Banpo pottery and reflect both everyday life and totemic belief in a settled farming community that also practiced gathering and fishing. This basin is regarded as a masterpiece of painted pottery. Similar examples were often used as lids for children\'s jar burials. The combined human-and-fish imagery is commonly interpreted as a shamanic image connected with ritual blessing, soul-calling, or fish totem worship.','Pottery','An early Neolithic painted pottery basin of the Yangshao culture, 16.5 cm high with a mouth diameter of 39.8 cm, unearthed in 1955 at Banpo, Xi\'an, Shaanxi. The red basin carries two symmetrical human-face-and-fish motifs painted in black on the inner wall, creating a vivid and imaginative composition.','Painted Pottery Basin','basin, painted, fish, human face, neolithic, ritual','Painted Pottery Basin with Human Face and Fish Pattern','Yangshao Culture','Neolithic Art',NULL,'manual','/assets/artifacts/human-face-fish-pattern-painted-basin.jpg',_binary '','/assets/artifacts/human-face-fish-pattern-painted-basin.jpg','In an ancient tribal site, people discovered a red pottery basin painted inside with eerie patterns where human faces and fish intertwine. It was not used to hold food, yet it was closely connected to the loss of children. These fantastical images were not painted for decoration, but for a special ritual.','这件红陶盆高16.5厘米，口径39.8厘米。半坡先民长期在河谷聚落中生活，以农业为主，兼营采集和渔猎，因此鱼纹成为常见的重要装饰。人面与鱼纹共存的奇特图像，既反映了当时的图腾观念，也展现出早期宗教活动与丧葬观念。','新石器时代前期仰韶文化彩陶精品，1955年出土于陕西西安半坡。盆内壁以黑彩绘出对称的人面鱼纹，构图自由而富有动感，被视为彩陶艺术代表作，并常被认为与儿童葬俗和巫师招魂祈福的仪式有关。','人面鱼纹彩陶盆','人面鱼纹彩陶盆','在远古的部落遗址中，人们发现了一件红陶盆，盆内壁画着人面与鱼儿交织的诡异图案。它并不是用来盛放食物，却与孩童的离去紧密相关。古人绘制这些奇幻纹样，不是为了装饰，而是为了完成一场特殊的仪式。'),(9,'The vessel combines sculpture and relief in an exceptional way, uniting animal imagery with ritual bronze design. Dense leiwen patterns cover the surface, while kui dragons, taotie bands, birds, and raised ridges intensify the visual rhythm. Its discovery in the Dongting Lake region also shows how far Shang bronze culture extended south of the Yellow River heartland.','Bronze','A Shang dynasty bronze square zun, 58.6 cm high and weighing 34.6 kilograms, unearthed in 1938 at Huangcai, Ningxiang, Hunan. It is the largest known Shang square zun and is celebrated for its powerful form and refined decoration. Four curled-horn rams are integrated into the shoulder, belly, and foot, giving the vessel both stability and movement.','Four-Ram Bronze Zun','zun, bronze, ram, ritual vessel, shang dynasty, relief','Square Zun with Four Rams','Shang Dynasty','Bronze Art',NULL,'manual','/assets/artifacts/four-ram-bronze-zun.jpg',_binary '','/assets/artifacts/four-ram-bronze-zun.jpg','Three thousand years ago, a grand bronze ritual vessel was carefully cast with four sacred rams rising from its body. It was the largest known example of its kind, created for supreme ritual use. Although born in the Central Plains, it was unearthed far away in a southern tribal region, quietly witnessing a hidden connection across distant lands.','四羊青铜方尊以细密云雷纹为地，颈部、肩部和圈足遍布夔龙纹、蕉叶纹、饕餮纹等装饰。它采用圆雕与浮雕结合的方式，将四羊与器身融为一体，是商代青铜工艺和礼制文化的典型代表，也证明商文化影响已深入长江以南地区。','商代青铜方尊中的杰作，1938年出土于湖南宁乡黄材。器身高58.6厘米，重34.6千克，四角巧妙结合卷角羊形，通体纹饰精丽，兼具雄奇气势与极高铸造水平。','四羊青铜方尊','四羊青铜方尊','三千年前，一件青铜重器被精心铸造，四只神羊盘踞其上，纹路繁复精美，是当时体量最大的同类器物。它诞生于中原王朝，却在千里之外的江南地区被发现，既承载着至高礼制，也见证了一段跨越地域的隐秘关联。'),(10,'This burner is an archaistic vessel in the Ge ware tradition. Authentic transmitted Ge ware pieces are rare and are mostly preserved in major museums. Fish-ear burners are among the classic forms associated with Southern Song ceramics, admired for their restrained shape, gentle glaze, and refined crackle surface.','Ceramic','A Ge ware fish-ear incense burner from the Song to Southern Song period, 8.8 cm high with a mouth diameter of 11.9 cm and a foot diameter of 9.2 cm. It has a slightly flaring mouth, constricted neck, rounded belly, ring foot, and distinctive fish-shaped handles. The glaze is soft beige with an all-over crackle pattern known as golden thread and iron wire.','Ge Ware Incense Burner','incense burner, ge ware, crackle glaze, fish ear, song dynasty','Ge Ware Fish-Ear Incense Burner','Song Dynasty','Ceramic Art',NULL,'manual','/assets/artifacts/ge-ware-fish-ear-incense-burner.jpg',_binary '','/assets/artifacts/ge-ware-fish-ear-incense-burner.jpg','In the Song dynasty, there was a porcelain incense burner with a warm and gentle glaze, yet its surface was covered with interlacing cracks. These cracks were not flaws from firing, but the very reason it was treasured. Elegant in form and rare in survival, it carried refined aesthetic ideals and was never just an ordinary household object.','此炉束颈、鼓腹、圈足，两侧作鱼形耳。哥窑器物存世极少，多收藏于重要博物馆之中。它并非普通日用瓷器，而是体现宋代审美趣味与仿古风尚的重要器物，开片纹理更被视为审美价值的一部分。','宋至南宋时期哥窑仿古器，炉高8.8厘米，口径11.9厘米。器身米黄色，釉色温润，布满开片，呈现“金丝铁线”特征，是传世哥窑瓷器中的珍品。','哥窑鱼耳瓷炉','哥窑鱼耳瓷炉','宋代有一件瓷炉，釉面温润，却布满了交错的裂纹。这些裂纹不是烧制的瑕疵，反而是它的珍贵之处。它造型雅致，存世稀少，承载着古人的审美追求，并非普通的生活用具。'),(11,'Length 8.9 cm, width 2.1 cm, height 3.4 cm. Reportedly unearthed in Lincheng, Shandong. Tiger tallies were official command credentials in early imperial China, used to transmit orders and authorize the movement of soldiers.','Bronze','A Qin dynasty bronze tiger tally used as a military authorization token. The small reclining tiger could be split into two matching halves, each engraved with the same inscription. Only when the emperor\'s half matched the general\'s half at Yangling could troops be mobilized.','Yangling Tiger Tally','tiger, small, split, inscribed','Yangling Tiger Tally','Qin Dynasty','Chinese Bronzes',NULL,'manual','/assets/artifacts/yangling-tiger-tally.jpg',_binary '','/assets/artifacts/yangling-tiger-tally.jpg','In the Qin dynasty, there was a small bronze tiger-shaped object that could command thousands of soldiers. It could be split into two halves, and each half bore the same mysterious inscription. The two halves belonged to different people, and only when they matched could its true power take effect.','虎符铭文写有“甲兵之符，右在皇帝，左在阳陵”，明确说明了它的使用制度。符节是中国古代朝廷传达命令、征调兵将的重要凭证，而阳陵虎符正是秦始皇军事权力高度集中的实物证明。','秦代调兵凭证，青铜铸成卧虎形，长8.9厘米。虎符可从中分为两半，左右两半分别由皇帝与驻军将领保管，调兵时须验合方可生效。','阳陵虎符','阳陵虎符','秦朝有一件青铜卧虎器物，体型小巧，却能调动千军万马。它可从中分为两半，每半都刻有相同的神秘铭文。它的两半分属不同的人，只有二者相合，才能发挥它真正的作用。'),(12,'Height 56 cm. Unearthed in 1957 at Tianhuishan, Chengdu, Sichuan. Such entertainers amused elite households with humorous, satirical, and improvised performances, often singing while beating a drum.','Pottery','An Eastern Han pottery figurine of a comic storyteller-drummer. Bare-chested and smiling, it hugs a flat drum with one arm and raises a drumstick with the other, capturing a lively performance scene.','Storytelling Drummer Figurine','figurine, drummer, performer, smiling','Storytelling Drummer Figurine','Eastern Han Dynasty','Ceramics',NULL,'manual','/assets/artifacts/storytelling-drummer-figurine.jpg',_binary '','/assets/artifacts/storytelling-drummer-figurine.jpg','In an Eastern Han tomb, a pottery figurine was found with a bare chest, a humorous expression, a drum tucked under one arm, and a stick raised in the other hand, as if lost in performance. It was neither a practical musical instrument nor a simple ritual offering, yet it reveals the entertainment culture of the aristocracy at the time.','汉代俳优常随侍贵族左右，以调谑、讽刺和滑稽表演取乐主人。画像石和墓葬陶俑中常见这类人物，说明说唱、乐舞与百戏在当时极为流行，这件击鼓说唱俑正是汉代娱乐文化的经典见证。','东汉陶俑，高56厘米，1957年出土于四川成都天回山。俑袒胸露腹，左臂抱鼓，右手举槌，张口嘻笑，动作夸张，生动刻画了汉代俳优说唱表演的形象。','击鼓说唱俑','击鼓说唱俑','东汉的一座墓葬中，出土了一尊陶俑。它袒胸露腹、神态诙谐，左手抱鼓、右手举槌，仿佛正沉浸在表演中。它并非实用乐器，却见证了当时贵族社会盛行的娱乐风尚。'),(13,'Height 85.4 cm, width 78 cm. Unearthed in 1987 in Guanghan, Sichuan. The mask has carrying holes at the sides and a tall central ornament, suggesting ceremonial use in sacrificial contexts rather than wearable use.','Bronze','A large bronze mask from Sanxingdui with rectangular features, protruding oval eyes, blade-like brows, a wide mouth, and flaring ears. It likely represented a divine being in ancient Shu ritual practice.','Sanxingdui Bronze Mask','mask, protruding eyes, ritual, large','Sanxingdui Bronze Mask','Shang Dynasty; Ancient Shu','Ritual Bronzes',NULL,'manual','/assets/artifacts/bronze-mask-sanxingdui.jpg',_binary '','/assets/artifacts/bronze-mask-sanxingdui.jpg','At the Sanxingdui site, archaeologists uncovered a huge object with an unusual face, protruding eyes, a broad mouth, halberd-shaped ears, and a tall ornament rising from its forehead. It was not meant to be worn. Instead, it was closely tied to the ritual life of the ancient Shu people and was regarded as the embodiment of a god.','三星堆遗址被视为古蜀祭祀坑遗存。这里出土的大量青铜器、玉器等文物，既具有鲜明地方特色，又明显受到中原文化影响。这类青铜面具通常被认为是古蜀人心中“神”的化身，可能与蜀王蚕丛形象有关。','三星堆出土的大型青铜面具，1987年出土于四川广汉。面具长方形脸、刀形粗眉、凸目阔口，额饰高耸，两侧还带有铸孔，被认为与古蜀祭祀活动密切相关。','青铜面具','青铜面具','三星堆遗址中，出土了一件巨大器具，面容奇特、凸目阔口，耳部呈戈形，额间有高耸装饰，上面还有便于扛抬的孔洞。它并非用于佩戴，而是与古蜀人的祭祀活动紧密相关，是某种“神”的化身。'),(14,'Length 182 cm. Unearthed in 1973 from Han Tomb No. 40 at Bajiaolang Village, Ding County, Hebei. The suit survived fire damage from tomb robbery and became even more colorful. Jade burial suits were divided by rank, with gold-thread examples reserved for the highest status in later systems.','Jade','A Western Han jade burial suit made from 1,203 jade plaques stitched together with about 2,567 grams of gold wire. Created for an aristocratic tomb occupant, it reflects the ancient belief that jade could preserve the body after death.','Gold-Thread Jade Burial Suit','burial suit, jade plaques, gold wire, funerary','Gold-Thread Jade Burial Suit','Western Han Dynasty','Jade and Funerary Art',NULL,'manual','/assets/artifacts/gold-thread-jade-burial-suit.jpg',_binary '','/assets/artifacts/gold-thread-jade-burial-suit.jpg','In a Western Han tomb, archaeologists discovered a funerary suit made from more than a thousand jade plaques and several kilograms of gold wire. Even after being scorched by fire, it became even more colorful. It was not created merely to display wealth, but because of an old belief, and in later dynasties its materials were strictly controlled by rank.','玉柙又称玉衣、玉匣，按缀线材料不同可分为金缕、银缕、铜缕和丝缕。东汉时期玉衣制度等级明确，而西汉尚未完全定型。这件金缕玉柙属于中山怀王刘修，虽历经火烧，色泽反而更加绚丽。','西汉高等级殓服，由1203片玉片和约2567克金丝编缀而成，1973年出土于河北定县汉墓。它体现了汉代“玉可使尸体不朽”的观念，是身份与礼制的重要象征。','金缕玉柙','金缕玉柙','西汉的一座墓葬中，出土了一件由上千片玉片和数千克金丝编缀而成的殓服。它历经火烧却色泽更显缤纷，是贵族死后所穿。古人打造这件器物，并非为了彰显财富，而是源于一个古老执念，而且它在不同朝代还有严格等级区分。'),(15,'Ming Wanli reign, 1573-1620. Total height 48.5 cm. Unearthed in 1957 from the Dingling Mausoleum in Beijing. The crown\'s lavish form does not fully match earlier court dress regulations, revealing changes in ceremonial practice by the late Ming. Its owner\'s childlessness also fed the succession dispute that deeply affected late Ming politics.','Crown','A spectacular Ming dynasty phoenix crown belonging to Empress Xiaoduan. Restored from the Dingling tomb, it is adorned with nine dragons, nine phoenixes, more than one hundred gemstones, and over four thousand pearls, showcasing extraordinary filigree, kingfisher feather inlay, gemstone setting, and pearl-threading techniques.','Empress Xiaoduan\'s Phoenix Crown','phoenix, crown, pearls, gemstones, imperial','Empress Xiaoduan\'s Phoenix Crown','Ming Dynasty','Imperial Costume and Jewelry',NULL,'manual','/assets/artifacts/empress-xiaoduan-phoenix-crown.jpg',_binary '','/assets/artifacts/empress-xiaoduan-phoenix-crown.jpg','In the Ming Dingling underground palace, archaeologists uncovered an elaborate phoenix crown set with thousands of pearls and gems. It belonged to an empress, and although magnificent, its design did not conform to the formal dress regulations of the time. Beyond its craftsmanship, it was closely tied to a major political controversy that shaped the late Ming court.','这件凤冠属于孝端皇后，造型华丽却与明代典制并不完全一致，反映出万历时期冠服制度已出现变化。它还与明末“国本之争”背景相连，因此不仅是工艺杰作，也承载着重要政治史意味。','明代万历时期皇后凤冠，1957年出土于北京定陵。冠体以漆竹为胎，饰九龙九凤，嵌宝石百余块、珍珠四千余颗，集花丝、点翠、镶嵌与穿系等复杂工艺于一体。','孝端皇后凤冠','孝端皇后凤冠','明代定陵地宫中，出土了一件镶嵌上千颗珠宝、工艺极致繁复的凤冠。它属于一位皇后，造型华丽却与当时的礼制规定并不完全相符。这件凤冠不仅承载着高超手工技艺，更与一场影响明末政局的重大争议紧密相关。'),(16,'Height 1.8 cm, side length 2.3 cm, weight 89.5 g. Unearthed between 1955 and 1960 at Shizhaishan, Jinning, Yunnan. Scholars have debated why the inscription was chiseled rather than cast, suggesting either an urgent imperial grant or a specially made substitute for transmission and burial.','Gold','A Western Han gold seal with a snake-shaped knob and the four-character inscription King of Dian. Its discovery confirmed the historical record that the Han court recognized the ruler of Dian and allowed him to continue governing the region under imperial authority.','King of Dian Gold Seal','seal, square, snake knob, inscription','King of Dian Gold Seal','Western Han Dynasty','Seals and Administrative Objects',NULL,'manual','/assets/artifacts/king-of-dian-gold-seal.jpg',_binary '','/assets/artifacts/king-of-dian-gold-seal.jpg','At a site in Yunnan, a gold seal with a snake-shaped knob was unearthed, its face engraved with four characters that confirmed a historical event recorded in ancient texts. The inscription was not made in the usual cast method, and the reason behind that choice hints at a special political purpose and a subtle connection between the Central Plains and the frontier.','《史记》记载汉武帝曾赐印滇王，使其继续统领滇民，这枚金印的出土印证了这一历史事实。其印文采用凿刻而非常规铸成，究竟是仓促封赐还是随葬仿制，长期是学界讨论的焦点。','西汉金印，高1.8厘米，边长2.3厘米，重89.5克，1955至1960年出土于云南晋宁石寨山。印为金质蛇钮，印面凿刻“滇王之印”四字，是中原王朝与滇国关系的重要物证。','“滇王之印”金印','“滇王之印”金印','云南一座遗址中，出土了一枚金质蛇钮印章，印面刻有四字铭文，印证了一段史书记载的历史。这枚金印的印文并非常规铸造，其制作方式背后藏着特殊原因，且它的存在见证了中原与边疆的隐秘关联。'),(17,'Dated to the reign of Marquis Zhao of Cai, 518-491 BCE. Unearthed in 1955 from the tomb of Marquis Zhao of Cai in Shouxian, Anhui. The bells are decorated with dense coiled-dragon motifs and identify themselves in inscription as xingzhong.','Bronze','A set of nine bronze chime bells from the Spring and Autumn period. Uniform in form but decreasing in size, each bell bears inscriptions and was capable of producing distinct tones, together forming a complete musical scale central to ritual music culture.','Chime Bells of Marquis Zhao of Cai','bells, musical, inscribed, ritual set','Chime Bells of Marquis Zhao of Cai','Spring and Autumn Period','Ritual Bronzes and Music',NULL,'manual','/assets/artifacts/chime-bells-of-marquis-zhao-of-cai.jpg',_binary '','/assets/artifacts/chime-bells-of-marquis-zhao-of-cai.jpg','In a Spring and Autumn period tomb, a group of nine bronze objects was discovered. They shared the same form but gradually decreased in size, and each one was inscribed with text. They were not ordinary display pieces: together they could sound different pitches and create a complete scale, carrying the ritual and musical culture of their age.','春秋时期编钟数量较西周进一步增加，礼乐制度也更趋完备。这组编钟自名“行钟”，不仅展现了当时高超的青铜铸造与装饰艺术，也为研究先秦音乐制度与礼仪文明提供了重要实物依据。','春秋时期一组九枚青铜编钟，1955年出土于安徽寿县蔡昭侯墓。九钟形制相同、大小依次递减，表面饰蟠螭纹并铸有铭文，能够发出不同音调，构成完整音阶。','编钟','编钟','春秋时期的一座墓葬中，出土了一组九枚青铜器物。它们形制相同、大小递减，表面布满细密纹饰，每一枚都刻有铭文。它们并非普通陈设，而能发出不同音调，构成完整音阶，承载着当时的礼乐文化。'),(18,'Height 35.8 cm, rim diameter 23.3 cm. Unearthed in 1958 at Taipingzhuang, Huaxian, Shaanxi, from the tomb of an adult woman together with bone daggers, stone tablets, axes, and other ritual-related objects. It may have been associated with sacrificial activity rather than everyday use.','Pottery','A Yangshao culture pottery ding shaped like a standing eagle. Its powerful body, hooked beak, and stable tripod stance merge sculptural animal form with the practical function of a vessel, making it one of the most striking examples of prehistoric pottery sculpture.','Eagle-Shaped Pottery Ding','eagle, ding, vessel, prehistoric, ritual','Eagle-Shaped Pottery Ding','Neolithic; Yangshao Culture','Prehistoric Ceramics',NULL,'manual','/assets/artifacts/eagle-shaped-pottery-ding.jpg',_binary '','/assets/artifacts/eagle-shaped-pottery-ding.jpg','At a Yangshao culture site, archaeologists found a pottery vessel shaped like a powerful eagle, with a strong body and commanding presence. It cleverly fused animal form with practical vessel design, and it was not an ordinary household object. Discovered in the tomb of an adult woman alongside multiple ritual objects, it hints at sacrificial practices among prehistoric communities.','鹰形陶鼎出土于一座成年女性墓葬，与石圭、骨匕等礼器共存，因此通常被认为与祭祀活动有关。它既是仰韶文化造型艺术与实用功能完美结合的代表，也说明先民在彩陶之外已经具备成熟的立体造型能力。','仰韶文化陶鼎，高35.8厘米，1958年出土于陕西华县太平庄。器物整体作雄鹰站立形态，鹰眼圆睁、钩喙有力，将动物雕塑感与鼎的功能巧妙结合。','鹰形陶鼎','鹰形陶鼎','仰韶文化遗址中，出土了一件雄鹰造型的陶制器物。鹰身健硕、神态威武，将动物造型与器物功能巧妙融合，并非普通的生活用具。它出土于成年女性墓葬，与多件礼器共存，背后藏着远古先民与祭祀相关的秘密。'),(19,'Late Shang dynasty, circa 14th-11th century BCE. Height 45.9 cm, weight 16.7 kg. Unearthed in 1976 from the tomb of Fu Hao at Yinxu, Anyang, Henan. Two owl-shaped zun were found together, reflecting the status, authority, and ritual world of this remarkable woman.','Bronze','A late Shang bronze zun in the form of an upright owl, cast with the inscription Fu Hao inside. Covered with dense motifs including dragons, snakes, and taotie, it is a masterwork of ancient Chinese bronze art and was used as a ritual wine vessel.','Owl-Shaped Bronze Zun of Fu Hao','owl, zun, ritual wine vessel, inscription','Owl-Shaped Bronze Zun of Fu Hao','Late Shang Dynasty','Ritual Bronzes',NULL,'manual','/assets/artifacts/owl-shaped-zun-of-fu-hao.jpg',_binary '','/assets/artifacts/owl-shaped-zun-of-fu-hao.jpg','In a Shang dynasty tomb, a pair of massive bronze vessels was unearthed in the form of fierce birds standing upright. Their surfaces were covered with complex motifs of dragons, snakes, and taotie, and two characters were cast inside. They were not ordinary display pieces, but ritual wine vessels deeply connected to the identity, power, and beliefs of a legendary woman.','鸮尊是商代异形鸟兽尊中的精品。这件器物以鸮的双足和下垂尾部构成稳定支点，构思奇巧，纹饰绮丽。铭文“妇好”直接指向商王武丁王后妇好，使其兼具礼器、身份与信仰象征的多重意义。','商代晚期青铜酒器，1976年出土于河南安阳殷墟妇好墓。整器作站立鸮形，通体布满云雷纹、夔龙纹、蛇纹和饕餮纹，器内铸有“妇好”铭文，是殷墟妇好墓最具代表性的重器之一。','“妇好”青铜鸮尊','“妇好”青铜鸮尊','商代墓葬中出土一对青铜重器，造型为昂首挺立的猛禽，通体布满龙、蛇、饕餮等繁复纹饰，器内铸有二字铭文。它不是普通陈设，而是与一位传奇女性的身份、权力和信仰紧密相关的酒器。'),(20,'Camel head height 58.4 cm, body length 43.4 cm, dancer height 25.1 cm. Unearthed in 1957 from the tomb of Xianyu Tinghui in Xi\'an, Shaanxi. The work likely represents a popular Chang\'an entertainment act combining music, acrobatics, trained animals, and strong Central Asian cultural influence.','Ceramic','A Tang dynasty sancai-glazed pottery camel carrying five performers, with one dancer in the center and four musicians seated around him. Its vivid glaze, elegant proportions, and animated composition make it one of the finest examples of Tang three-color ceramic art.','Sancai-Glazed Camel with Musicians','camel, musicians, dancer, sancai, performance','Sancai-Glazed Camel with Musicians','Tang Dynasty','Tang Ceramics',NULL,'manual','/assets/artifacts/sancai-glazed-camel-with-musicians.jpg',_binary '','/assets/artifacts/sancai-glazed-camel-with-musicians.jpg','In a Tang dynasty tomb, archaeologists found a sancai-glazed object shaped as a proud standing camel. On its back sat five Han and non-Han performers, some dancing and some playing music. Its bright glaze and vivid design mark it as a masterpiece of its kind, and it does not depict an ordinary daily scene, but rather a difficult performance once popular in Chang\'an.','这件作品表现的并非普通运输场景，而是盛唐长安百戏与胡乐文化的缩影。唐代都城聚集了来自中亚、西域乃至更远地区的乐工和舞者，骆驼载乐的节目正反映出开放包容又高度繁荣的都市文化景观。','唐代三彩杰作，1957年出土于陕西西安鲜于庭诲墓。昂首骆驼背上载有五位艺人，中间一人舞蹈，其余围坐演奏，造型夸张生动，釉色鲜明润泽，代表唐三彩极高水平。','三彩釉陶载乐骆驼','三彩釉陶载乐骆驼','唐代墓葬中，出土了一件三彩器物，造型是昂首挺立的骆驼，驼背上载着五位汉胡艺人，或舞或奏，釉色鲜明、造型生动，代表了当时该类工艺的最高水平。它展现的并非日常场景，而是长安城中盛行的一种高难度节目。'),(21,'Height 16.2 cm, about 70 g. Unearthed in 1981 in Inner Mongolia. Buyao ornaments were important ancient women\'s headdresses, named for the way their suspended decorations swayed while the wearer walked. This example reflects both Central Plains traditions and northern steppe animal imagery.','Gold','A Northern Dynasties gold buyao headdress with a horse-head base and branching deer-antler forms tipped with dangling gold leaves. Inlaid ornaments enrich its nomadic grassland character while preserving the elegant motion expected of elite women\'s headwear.','Horse-Head Deer-Antler Gold Buyao','headdress, horse head, deer antlers, dangling leaves','Horse-Head Deer-Antler Gold Buyao','Northern Dynasties','Ancient Jewelry',NULL,'manual','/assets/artifacts/horse-head-deer-antler-gold-buyao.jpg',_binary '','/assets/artifacts/horse-head-deer-antler-gold-buyao.jpg','At a Northern Dynasties site, a gold headdress was discovered with a horse head at its base and deer-antler-like branches rising upward. Small gold leaves hung from the tips and swayed with movement, while bead inlays added to its striking grassland style. It was not a simple ornament, but an important women\'s headdress that blended the aesthetics of different regions.','步摇是中国古代妇女的重要头饰之一，战国时期已有文献记载，魏晋南北朝时尤为流行。北方游牧民族喜用羊、马、鹿等草原动物作为装饰主题，这件作品正体现出中原传统与北方草原审美的融合。','北朝金质头饰，高16.2厘米，1981年出土于内蒙古。步摇以马头为基座，向上分出鹿角形枝杈，梢头悬挂金叶并镶嵌珠饰，佩戴时会随着步履轻轻摇曳。','马头鹿角形金步摇','马头鹿角形金步摇','北朝时期的遗址中，出土了一件金质头饰，以马头为基座，分出鹿角形枝杈，梢头悬着可晃动的金叶，镶嵌着珠饰，造型兼具草原特色。它并非普通饰物，佩戴时会随步履摇曳，是当时妇女的重要头饰，且融合了不同地域的审美。'),(22,'Height 133 cm, rim length 110 cm, rim width 79 cm. Unearthed in 1939 at Wuguan Village, Anyang, Henan. Weighing 832.84 kg, it required more than one thousand kilograms of metal and extremely complex casting organization, demonstrating the extraordinary scale and sophistication of late Shang bronze civilization.','Bronze','The Houmuwu Bronze Square Ding is a monumental ritual vessel from the reign of King Wu Ding of the Shang dynasty. Massive, solemn, and densely decorated, it remains the heaviest known ancient Chinese bronze object, with an inscription inside naming Houmuwu, the temple title of the king\'s mother.','Houmuwu Bronze Square Ding','ding, square vessel, monumental, inscription, ritual','Houmuwu Bronze Square Ding','Shang Dynasty','Ritual Bronzes',NULL,'manual','/assets/artifacts/houmuwu-bronze-square-ding.jpg',_binary '','/assets/artifacts/houmuwu-bronze-square-ding.jpg','At a Shang dynasty site, archaeologists uncovered a gigantic and solemn bronze square ding, the heaviest known bronze vessel from ancient China. Its surface is covered with intricate motifs, and three characters were cast on the inner wall. The effort required to cast it was enormous, and the vessel not only proves the high development of Shang bronze culture, but is also closely tied to a relative of a Shang king.','鼎腹内壁铸有“后母戊”三字，被认为是商王母亲的庙号。整器纹饰繁复，铸造时所需金属原料超过一吨，充分说明商代后期青铜铸造的组织规模、技术复杂度和礼制水平都已达到极高程度。','商王武丁时期巨型青铜方鼎，1939年出土于河南安阳武官村。器高133厘米，重832.84千克，是目前已知中国古代最重的青铜器，气势雄伟庄严。','“后母戊”青铜方鼎','“后母戊”青铜方鼎','商代遗址中，出土了一件体型巨大、雄伟庄严的青铜方鼎，是目前已知中国古代最重的青铜器，器身布满繁复纹饰，内壁铸有三字铭文。它的铸造工艺复杂，耗费原料巨大，见证了商代青铜文明的高度发达，且与一位商王的亲人紧密相关。'),(23,'Height 26 cm. Unearthed in 1971 at Saqintala, Ongniud Banner, Inner Mongolia. Many Neolithic sites preserve dragon-like imagery, but this curled jade form most closely matches the giant head, curved body, and sacred beast characteristics later associated with dragons in Chinese tradition.','Jade','A finely carved Hongshan culture jade dragon with a body curled like a hook. Celebrated as the First Dragon of China, it is widely regarded as one of the earliest and most important physical forms behind the later Chinese dragon image.','Hongshan Jade Dragon','dragon, curled, carved, prehistoric, sacred','Hongshan Jade Dragon','Hongshan Culture','Prehistoric Jade',NULL,'manual','/assets/artifacts/hongshan-jade-dragon.jpg',_binary '','/assets/artifacts/hongshan-jade-dragon.jpg','At a Hongshan culture site, a beautifully carved jade object was unearthed, its body curled like a hook and honored as the First Dragon of China. It was not just an ordinary decorative piece. Behind it lies the spiritual world of prehistoric communities, and it also helps confirm the early image of the dragon itself.','新石器时代多个遗址中都出现过与龙有关的图像或造型，而红山文化玉龙最符合巨头、有角、曲身的神兽特征。它不仅是一件精美玉器，更反映了远古先民的神灵观念与精神信仰。','红山文化玉器，1971年出土于内蒙古翁牛特旗赛沁塔拉。玉龙躯体卷曲如钩，雕琢精美，被誉为“中华第一龙”，常被视为中国龙形象的早期源头。','玉龙','玉龙','红山文化遗址中，出土了一件雕琢精美的玉器，躯体卷曲如钩，有着“中华第一龙”的美誉，是龙的原始形态。它并非普通的装饰摆件，背后藏着远古先民的信仰，且印证了龙的早期形象。');
